# Repository Package Structure

Use this contract directly. Repository files and installed types are
authoritative. A separately installed global `package-structure` skill may
provide a safe renderer or extra validation, but this workflow does not depend
on its filesystem path.

## Establish ownership

1. Read `AGENTS.md`, the profile in `references/repository-profile.md`, the
   affected package `README*`, and only the owners routed from `docs/README.md`
   for the change (normally package ownership, Effect services, and quality).
2. Inspect the worktree and preserve unrelated changes.
3. Name the capability, callers, untrusted boundaries, and runtime owner.
   Reject a new package for one-use code, a pass-through wrapper, or a generic
   helper bucket.
4. Use `__SCOPE__/*` names and place `__SOURCE_CONDITION__` before `types`
   and `default` in development exports. Publish exports must omit the source
   condition and be proven from the actual packed artifact when publishable.

## Package contract

An Effect service package separates:

```text
src/schemas.ts              Schemas, brands, and schema-derived types
src/errors.ts               expected tagged failures
src/service.ts              Context.Service contract and named operations only
src/live.layer.ts           private production SDK/config/resource implementation
src/test.layer.ts           deterministic substitution at the same contract
src/__testing__/            reusable fixtures and observations only
test/                       behavior and boundary tests
```

RPC and HTTP API packages depend inward on the domain service and own only
transport contracts, handlers, named application clients, and transport Layers.
They never duplicate domain policy or expose a generated/raw client.

## Effect and composition rules

- Keep primary Effects lazy, flat, readable, composable, and sequential.
- Keep one-use mapping, decoding, and typed error handling beside the operation.
  Extract only demonstrated reuse, independently tested policy, real I/O, or
  resource lifetime; forbid pass-through helpers and `utils` dumping grounds.
- Decode unknown input/output once at ingress and encode only at outward
  transport, provider, persistence, or reporting boundaries.
- Reuse owning Schemas, schema-derived types, branded identifiers, services,
  Layers, and tagged errors.
- Load semantic configuration through Schema-backed `Config`/`ConfigProvider`
  and keep secrets redacted until immediate use.
- Reject generic SDK callbacks, raw clients, raw `id: string`, primitive
  semantic config, `instanceof` policy, unchecked provider output, and package
  runtime execution.
- Keep route/feature orchestration in the app and focused React leaves narrow
  and service-unaware.
- Update the owning architecture page and affected critical journey/proof in the
  same slice as any public schema, service, or transport change. Route real
  operations to runbooks; do not make a package README a competing owner.

## Verify

Run focused package tests and the repository's real ordered gate:

```bash
bun run verification
```

Also run applicable package build, export-consumer, packed-artifact, integration,
and downstream checks. Report the ownership decision, exports, Layers,
documentation/proof impact, exact commands, and any path-specific exception.
